level.text:
Whenever a taxicab operator ceases to be for hire and is proceeding to a place without intending to take on passengers, the operator shall display a sign reading &#8220;Off Duty&#8221; or &#8220;Out of Service,&#8221; whichever is
      appropriate under these regulations, and turn off the cruising light. The operator shall enter on the manifest &#8220;Out of Service&#8221; or &#8220;Off Duty,&#8221; and the time and location; provided, that the &#8220;Off Duty&#8221;
      sign shall not be displayed during rush hours between 7:00 a.m. and 9:30 a.m., and 4:00 p.m. and 6:30 p.m.
